Module fi.tuni.prog3.sisufxml
Package fi.tuni.prog3.sisufxml

Class DataStructure

java.lang.Object
fi.tuni.prog3.sisufxml.DataStructure
public class DataStructure extends Object
A class representing a data structure, that consists of ModuleEntry objects. Has the functions needed to initialize, modify and/or expand the structure. Uses Sisu API as a source for the module data and information.
Author:
Arttu

    • getDegrees

      public void getDegrees()
      Downloads a json file that includes all the root degrees. Creates a list of these JsonObjects, and assigns this list to be this DataStructures degrees.

    • populateDataStruct

      public void populateDataStruct()
      Populates the DataStructure with the information found inside the different degrees, downloaded from Sisu. Creates ModuleEntries from all of them, and adds them to this DataStructures moduleList.

    • creditsToParent

      public static void creditsToParent(ModuleEntry m, int op, String addremove)
      Sends the credits of a module to its parent, in order to change its completed credits accordingly. Works recursively until the root module.
      Parameters:
      m - The child module.
      op - Credits.
      addremove - Tells wether the credits need to be added or removed.
